<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_g0ylævzag" xml:lang="os">
    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma">
        <orth>g˳ylævzag</orth>
    </form>
    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal">
        <orth>kʼwælævzag</orth>
    </form>
    <sense>
        <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>косноязычный</q>
        </cit>
        <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>inarticulate</q>
        </cit>
    </sense>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>ærbakodtoj jæm kʼ˳yrma g˳ylævzagy</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>привели к нему глухого косноязычного</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>there some people brought to him a man who was deaf and could hardly talk</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <ref target="#src_Марк"/>
                <biblScope>%i7%i 32</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>ærbakodtoj jæm kʼ˳yrma g˳ylævzagy</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>привели к нему глухого косноязычного</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>there some people brought to him a man who was deaf and could hardly talk</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <ref target="#src_Марк"/>
                <biblScope>%i7%i 32</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Во второй части — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævzag"/> (<ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_yvzag"/>) ‘язык’. Первая часть, %ig˳yl%i, не имеет отношения к <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_g0yl"/> ‘пирог’; ее следует сближать с элементом %ikur%i,
        %ikul%i, %igul%i (см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_k0yr-"/>) в названиях телесных
        недостатков: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_k0yræfcæg"/> ‘короткошейный’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_cænk0yl"/> ‘безрукий’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼ0ylyx"/> ‘хромой’,
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼ0yrma"/> ‘глухой’, д. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_gulu"/> ‘безрогий’ и др. Для д. %ikʼwæl-%i ср. еще д. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_kʼwælli"/> ‘мозоль’, ‘волдырь’.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">In the second part of the word there is <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævzag"
        /> (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_yvzag"/>) ‘tongue’. The first part, %ig˳yl%i, is not
        related to <ref type="xr" target="#entry_g0yl"/> ‘pie’; it should rather be connected to the
        element %ikur%i, %ikul%i, %igul%i (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_k0yr-"/>) in the
        infirmity names: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_k0yræfcæg"/> ‘shortnecked’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_cænk0yl"/> ‘armless’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼ0ylyx"/> ‘limp’,
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼ0yrma"/> ‘deaf’, Digor <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_gulu"/> ‘hornless’ etc. For Digor %ikʼwæl-%i cf. also Digor <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_kʼwælli"/> ‘callosity’, ‘blister’.</etym>
</entry>
